<h1>Legal Disclaimer</h1>

<h2>Not Legal Advice</h2>
<p>The HR Compliance Database ("the Database") is provided for <strong>informational purposes only</strong>. The information contained in this database does not constitute legal advice and should not be relied upon as such.</p>

<h2>No Attorney-Client Relationship</h2>
<p>Use of this database does not create an attorney-client relationship between you and the maintainers of this project, Zivtech or any of its employees, contractors, or contributors.</p>

<h2>Accuracy and Currency</h2>
<p>While we strive to keep the information in this database accurate and up-to-date:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Labor laws change frequently through legislative action, regulatory rulemaking, and court decisions.</li>
  <li>There may be delays between when a law changes and when this database is updated.</li>
  <li>Each regulation record includes a "Last Verified" date — check this to assess data freshness.</li>
  <li>The database may contain errors, omissions, or outdated information.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Verify Against Official Sources</h2>
<p><strong>Always verify the information in this database against official sources before relying on it for compliance decisions.</strong> Each regulation record includes links to official source material. Use those links to confirm the current state of the law.</p>

<h2>Scope Limitations</h2>
<ul>
  <li>This database covers scheduling-related labor laws (overtime, breaks, scheduling, minor labor). It does not cover all areas of employment law.</li>
  <li>Coverage is limited to U.S. federal, state, and select local jurisdictions.</li>
  <li>Industry-specific exemptions and exceptions may not be fully captured.</li>
  <li>Collective bargaining agreements (CBAs) may override or modify the regulations described here.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Consult Qualified Counsel</h2>
<p>For compliance decisions affecting your organization, consult with a qualified employment law attorney who is familiar with the specific jurisdictions and circumstances relevant to your situation.</p>

<h2>Open Source Contributions</h2>
<p>This database is maintained as an open-source project. Data is contributed by community members and reviewed by maintainers. Contributors are not warranting the accuracy of their contributions. See individual regulation records for contributor information.</p>

<h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
<p>The maintainers of this database, including Zivtech and all contributors, shall not be held liable for any damages, penalties, fines, or other losses arising from reliance on information contained in this database.</p>
